MultiPixel Security & Anti-Cheat Policy
Relimintor (Raptor4 / MultiPixel)

1. PURPOSE
This policy defines what constitutes cheating and how MultiPixel enforces
security.

2. PROHIBITED BEHAVIOR
• cheats
• exploits
• hacks
• automation tools
• bots
• packet manipulation
• replay tools
• proxies that alter traffic
• modified clients
• custom launchers
• bypassing anti-cheat
• memory editing
• code injection

3. DETECTION METHODS
MultiPixel may use:
• behavioral analysis
• packet validation
• integrity checks
• server-side verification
• anomaly detection

4. CONSEQUENCES
• temporary bans
• permanent bans
• server bans
• mod removal
• legal action (for severe cases)

5. APPEALS
Users may submit appeals, but MultiPixel is not obligated to reverse bans.

6. SERVER REQUIREMENTS
Servers must:
• enforce anti-cheat
• ban cheaters
• report major exploits
